    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0211"/>
        		<head>Jim to Mlle. Marcelle Guerin <date value="1915-12-28">[Dec 28th 1915]</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1915-12-28">[December 28th, 1915]</date></dateline>
        			
            <salute>
            Dear Marcelle.
            </salute></opener>
        		
        		<p>
            Just a hurried 
            note to tell you that
            I have tried the
            famous La Cloche table
            d’hote.  Excellent, tho [sic]
            I made a mistake and
            didn’t get at the long
            table.  I discovered myself
            at a small table in a 
            room where sat a maidenly
            lady some few years
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0212" n="[p.2]"/>
            
            older that God, and a fat
            old Colonel.  Nevertheless I
            enjoyed it to the tune 
            of enough to have bought
            out the place, and
            now I am waiting for
            the train to whisk me
            back to Paris and
            from thence to Pau.
            Had an amusing time
            at the aviation camp
            here.  They tried to force
            all sorts of uniforms &mdash;
            shoes &mdash; hats and shirts
            on me, but I took ^only  a
            blue kepi because I  
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0213" n="[p.3]"/>
            
            look funny in it &mdash;
            A blue coat because 
            it is so gay &mdash; A
            blue tunic because
            it looks so rotten &mdash;
            put on my khaki
            and went my way
            rejoicing, after seeing
            a machine come down
            to “casse la genle” of the 
            would be “pilote”.
            </p><p>
            I love the idea of
            being sent back to
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0214" n="[p.4]"/>
            
            Paris to take the
            train for Pau.  They 
            thought they would
            give me a treat and
            let me see the big
            city, not knowing
            I had enjoyed it
            for over twenty days.  
            They couldn’t figure
            me out &mdash; Called me
            a “drole type” &mdash; and
            wondered from where 
            I had escaped.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>Best</salute> 
            <signed>Jim</signed>
        		</closer>
        		
            
